In this article you can learn how to check the bandwidth on your account for multiple devices within MyRackspace Portal.


### Prerequisites

Viewing this data requires specific device level permissions. If you experience issues viewing the bandwidth usage on your firewall device, please ensure you have appropriate permissions on the device or raise a ticket for Rackspace support.


### Procedure (repeat as necessary)

1. Log in to the MyRackspace Portal by using your name and password.

2. In the top navigation bar, click a Product > Dedicated Hosting.

3. At the top of the panel, select Network > Bandwidth.

4. A bandwidth report for the current month will be displayed, you can change that on the drop down menu where you can select which month to view.


On the top navigation bar, you can access other reports, like Device Bandwidth, Bandwidth Data or MRTG Graphs, where you can filter the information you need.
